  title: Why use `Time.deltaTime` for fuel consumption?
  text: Because `Update()` runs every frame, and not all computers run at the same
    framerate. Without `Time.deltaTime`, someone running at 120 FPS would use fuel
    way faster than someone at 30 FPS. With `deltaTime`, everyone loses fuel at the
    same rate, 1 unit per second, regardless of framerate.
